.V= $Header: getpagesize.2 1.5 86/05/13 $
.TH GETPAGESIZE 2 "\*(V)" "4BSD"
.SH NAME
getpagesize \- get system page size
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.ft 3
pagesize = getpagesize()
int pagesize;
.ft 1
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.I Getpagesize
returns the number of bytes in a page.
Page granularity is the granularity of many of the memory
management calls.
.PP
The page size is a 
.I system
page size and may not be the same as the underlying
hardware page size.
.SH SEE ALSO
sbrk(2), pagesize(1)
